Package com.example.fitnesstracker

Class ObjectActiveWorkout

java.lang.Object
com.example.fitnesstracker.ObjectActiveWorkout
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class ObjectActiveWorkout extends Object implements Serializable
Class representing an active workout session. It contains information about the workout name, date, and the sets of lifts (ObjectLiftSets) performed during the workout.
Author:
Miles Nichols

    • addLiftSet

      public void addLiftSet(List<ObjectSet> sets, String liftName)
      Adds or updates the sets (reps and weight) for a specific lift by its name. If the lift already exists in the workout, its sets are updated. If the lift doesn't exist, a new lift set is created and added.
      Parameters:
      sets - The list of sets (ObjectSet) to add or update.
      liftName - The name of the lift to add or update sets for.
